Servlet Listeners 
1. Servlet listeners allow servlets to react to certain events in the web application, and 
   then take appropriate 
   action if required 
2. These events can be:
	a. requests - creating and destroying when a user request comes in
	b. sessions - creating and destroying user sessions
	c. context - a web application being loaded and unloaded from the application container 
	d. handling asynchronous events (i.e on-complete, on-start